# one sample of 50
n <- 50
s <- sample_n(d, size = n, replace = FALSE)

# mean, standard deviation, standard error, and confidence interval for each variable

# mean, standard deviation, standard error, and confidence interval for height

mean(s$height)
## [1] 66.9518
sd(s$height)
## [1] 4.096925
height_se <- sd(s$height)/(sqrt(n))

height_se
## [1] 0.5793927
m_height <- mean(s$height)


percent_ci <- 95
alpha <- 1 - percent_ci / 100
lower <- m_height + qnorm(alpha / 2) * height_se
upper <- m_height + qnorm(1 - alpha / 2) * height_se
(ci <- c(lower, upper))
## [1] 65.81622 68.08739
ci
## [1] 65.81622 68.08739
# We are 95% sure that the population mean of height is between 67.12372 and 69.23766.
